Durban - Three people have sustained burn wounds after coming into contact with chemicals at their workplace in the industrial area of Teakwood Road in Clairwood, south of Durban on Tuesday night. Rescue Care Paramedics spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said when they arrived on the scene they found the Durban Fire Department and SAPS in attendance. "Apparently the three were working when chemicals mixed and there was some sort of explosion. The three men were treated on the scene and were then transported to a nearby hospital for the further care that they required,"Â Jamieson said. At this stage, the events leading up to the explosion is unknown however SAPS and Durban Fire Department will be investigating further. The police and the fire department could not provide any further details on the incident. Attempts to find the company where the incident happened was fruitless. Jamieson said the injured are still in hospital on Wednesday. Daily News